abstract.abstracttext:
Of the 115 eyes, 57 received 5-Fluorouracil while 58 received Mitomycin C. A target Intraocular Pressure of 21 mmHg at 6 months was achieved in 53 of 56 (

 95%

) eyes in the 5-Fluorouracil group and 54 of 57 (

 95%

) eyes in the Mitomycin C group (P = 1.00). At 12 months, 45 of 48 (94%) eyes in the 5-Fluorouracil group met a target Intraocular Pressure of 21 mmHg while 48 of 54 (89%) eyes in the Mitomycin C group did (P =.49). The most common complications in each group were persistent choroidal effusions and bleb leak.
